  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/758",
  "title": "hits widget exception with table tags",
  "body": "If you try to use table tags in the hits widget template like this:\n\n`search.addWidget(\n        instantsearch.widgets.hits({\n          container: '#hits-container',\n          templates: {\n            empty: 'No events found',\n            item: '<tr><td><a href=\"{{view_uri}}\">{{event_number}}</a></td><td><a href=\"{{view_uri}}\" target=\"_new\">{{name}}</a></td><td>{{startdaypart_name}}</td><td>{{duration_name}}</td><td>{{room_name}}</td><td><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign\" data-toggle=\"tooltip\" title=\"{{description}}\"></span></td></tr>'\n          },\n        })\n      );`\n\nYou'll get this error:\n\n**Minified exception occurred; use the non-minified dev environment for the full error message and additional helpful warnings.**\n\nHere's a JS Fiddle that shows it happening.\n\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/qkqzgsv9/\n\nI've documented my process for finding this on this stack overflow question:  http://stackoverflow.com/questions/34515559/algolia-instantsearch-js-minified-exception-occurred-invariant\n\nIt doesn't happen if you use `div` tags rather than `tr` and `td` tags\n",
